Package tree

Class GenericTree<TREETYPE>

  • java.lang.Object
    • tree.GenericTree<TREETYPE>
  • Type Parameters:
    TREETYPE - The typeparemter for the GenericTree. It is replaced with the concrete type during instantiation.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDeepCopy, ITree<TREETYPE>, ISearchableByFilter<ITreeNode<TREETYPE>>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ProductTree
    public class GenericTree<TREETYPE>
extends Object
implements ITree<TREETYPE>
    This class handles a simple tree-structure of ITreeNodes. It serves as an entry point and contains the first (root) ITreeNode of the ITree. All subsequent entries are either directly or indirectly connected to this root ITreeNode.

    All ITreeNodes that are used in this GenericTree have the same type. This means, that there are only GenericTrees allowed that contain ITreeNodes of the same type. However, the type of the GenericTree and its ITreeNodes can be decided during instantiation.

    OOP

      • findNode

        public ITreeNode<TREETYPE> findNode​(TREETYPE searchValue)
        This method traverses the ITree and searches for the passed value. If a matching ITreeNode is found, the return value is the ITreeNode, otherwise it is NULL.

        First the root ITreeNode is checked via the ITreeNode.checkNodeByValue(Object) method and returned if the passed search value matches. Otherwise, the ITreeNode.findNodeByValue(Object) method is invoked on the root ITreeNode and the result of the invocation is returned.

        Specified by:
        findNode in interface ITree<TREETYPE>
        Parameters:
        searchValue - The value used to identify the searched ITreeNode.
        Returns:
        the ITreeNode if found, or NULL otherwise.

      • findNode

        public ITreeNode<TREETYPE> findNode​(ITreeNode<TREETYPE> searchNode)
        This method traverses the ITree and searches for the passed node. If a matching ITreeNode is found, the return value is the ITreeNode, otherwise it is NULL.

        First the root ITreeNode is checked via the Object.equals(Object) method and returned if the passed ITreeNode matches. Otherwise, the ITreeNode.findNodeByNode(ITreeNode) method is invoked on the root ITreeNode and the result of the invocation is returned.

        Specified by:
        findNode in interface ITree<TREETYPE>
        Parameters:
        searchNode - The node used to identify the searched ITreeNode.
        Returns:
        the ITreeNode if found, or NULL otherwise.

      • searchByFilter

        public Collection<ITreeNode<TREETYPE>> searchByFilter​(ISearchFilter filter,
                                                      Object compareObject)
        The ISearchableByFilter.searchByFilter(util.searchable.ISearchFilter, java.lang.Object) method is called on the root ITreeNode if it is not NULL. In this case the result of the method call is returned. If the root ITreeNode is NULL, an empty Collection is returned.

        All implementations of this interface allow searching for one or many matching objects in its context using ISearchFilter.searchFilterFunction(Object, Object).

        The filter is applied on features, determined by the implementing class, and evaluates if it matches the passed compare object. Each matching feature is added to a Collection and returned.

        Specified by:
        searchByFilter in interface ISearchableByFilter<TREETYPE>
        Parameters:
        filter - the ISearchFilter used to search
        compareObject - the object that is used for comparison
        Returns:
        a Collection of objects matching the filter function

      • deepCopy

        public ITree<TREETYPE> deepCopy()
        Creates a copy of the GenericTree and all its attributes and returns it. All attributes that implement the IDeepCopy interface have to be copied via the IDeepCopy.deepCopy() method as well.

        Creates and returns a copy of this object. The precise meaning of "copy" may depend on the class of the object. The general intent is that, for any object x, the expression: 

         x.deepCopy() != x
        will be true, and that the expression: 
         x.deepCopy().getClass() == x.getClass()
        will be true, but these are not absolute requirements. While it is typically the case that: 
         x.deepCopy().equals(x)
        will be true, this is not an absolute requirement.
